Definition of entropy

Entropy was a measure introduced by Claude Shannon (1948,A Mathematical Theory of Communication) to measure the amount of uncertainty in a signal.

The entropy \(H\) is defined as: \[ H(X)=-\sum\limits_{x=1}^np(x)\log_2p(x) \] \(X\) is a discrete random variable and \(f(x)\) is the value of its probability distribution at \(x\) Because of \(log_2\) entropy is measured in bits.

Entropy in BOLD responses \[ H(B)=-\sum\limits_{b\in B}p(b)\log_2p(b) \]

\(B\) is the range of BOLD response within a ROI, depends how many bins we defined Here we caculated the Entroy of BOLD respnse (\(H(B)\)) of one voxel with 6 orientations (-90, -45, 0, 45, 90, 180) ## need to figure out whether to add 180 (back side of face) ##

3rd step: entropy of the ALL BOLD responses in each voxel 3.1 discretizing the continuous BOLD response into dscrete variable \(B\) by dividing the range of responses into a set of equidistant bins \(b\) nBins range is based on all voxels within a ROI 3.2 entropy of the BOLD responses in each voxel 4rd step: entropy of the each orientations of a voxel

  ROI_range <- range(RandomVox_Zdata$zSigCh)
  kdebins <- ceiling(diff(ROI_range)/kdeball$h) # define bin from kde

computeVox_entropy <- function(Sig, numBins=kdebins, MImethod="ML"){
  BOLD_discreted <- discretize(Sig, numBins=numBins,r=ROI_range)
  HB_perVox <- entropy::entropy(BOLD_discreted, unit="log2", method = MImethod)
  return(HB_perVox)
  }

The definition of Mutual information \[ H(X;Y) = -\sum\limits_{x\in X}\sum\limits_{y\in Y}p(x,y)\log_2p(x,y)/p(x)p(y) H(X;Y) = H(X) - H(X|Y) = H(Y) - H(Y|X) = H(X) + H(Y) - H(X,Y) \]

\(H(X), H(Y)\) is marginal entropy of X,Y; \(H(X|Y)\) is conditional entropy of X given Y; \(H(X,Y)\) is joint entroy of X and Y

Mutual information in BOLD responses \[ H(B;\Theta) = H(B) - H(B|\Theta) = H(B) + H(\Theta) - H(B,\Theta) \] \(\Theta\) is the indvidual orientation that we presented

The definition of conditional entropy \[ H(Y|X) = -\sum\limits_{x\in X}p(x) H(Y|X = x) = -\sum\limits_{x\in X}p(x)\sum\limits_{y\in Y}p(y|x)\log_2p(y|x) = -\sum\limits_{x\in X}\sum\limits_{y\in Y}p(x,y)\log_2p(y|x) \]

Conditonal Entropy of orientations in BOLD responses \[ H(B|\Theta) = -\sum\limits_{\theta\in \Theta}p(\theta)\sum\limits_{b\in B}p(b|\theta)\log_2p(b|\theta) = -\sum\limits_{b\in B}\sum\limits_{\theta\in \Theta}p(\theta,b)\log_2p(b|\theta) \] \(\Theta\) is the indvidual orientation that we presented, computed condtional entropy \(p(b|\theta)\), which measure the resp uncertainty given knowlegde of the stimulus orientation

MI_table <- merge(HB, HBtheta, by="voxel")
